messages.content: What is WAS Node Suite?
WAS Node Suite is a GUI that uses a stable diffusion model to generate images and videos, with many new nodes for image processing, text processing, and more.
How can I share workflows with the WAS Node Suite community?
You can share workflows to the workflows wiki by providing embedded PNGs with workflows, or JSON files.
Can I donate to the project to help its continued development?
Yes, you can donate to the project via the provided PayPal link.
Is WAS-Node Suite under active development?
No, as of 12/15/2023, WAS-Node Suite is not under active development. However, the author welcomes forks and PRs for continued development.
What is the purpose of the ASCII node?
The ASCII node has been deprecated in favor of the STRING node to provide more clarity about the data being passed.
What does the Image Aspect Ratio node do?
The Image Aspect Ratio node fetches the aspect ratio of an input image in float format.
What is the role of the WAS_Node_Suite.py file?
The WAS_Node_Suite.py file is the main script for the WAS Node Suite, which is used to install and manage the suite's nodes.
What does the BLIP Model Loader node do?
The BLIP Model Loader node loads a BLIP model to input into the BLIP Analyze node.
What is the purpose of the BLIP Analyze Image node?
The BLIP Analyze Image node gets a text caption from an image, or interrogates the image with a question using a BLIP model.
What does the MiDaS Depth Approximation node do?
The MiDaS Depth Approximation node produces a depth approximation of a single image input.
What are custom tokens used for in WAS Node Suite ComfyUI?
Custom tokens can be used in the Save Text File and Save Image nodes to dynamically generate file names based on system data.
What are the requirements for installing video nodes on a Windows system?

For Windows installations, you need to download the proper FFMPEG binaries for your system and set the FFMPEG path in the config file, as well as download OpenH264 1.8.0 and place it in the root of ComfyUI.
What are the limitations of the Image Crop Face node?
Sometimes no faces are found in badly generated images, or faces at angles, and sometimes face crop is black if the padding is too large and intersects with the image edge.
